  "text": "Stepwise regression is among the unsatisfactory techniques for reasons summarized by Montgomery and Peck (1992) in section 7.2.3, as well as [CITATION_1] . Regardless of their relative merits, a practical limitation is that they do not reflect the strength of empirical evidence that the most important independent variable has been chosen. One strategy is to test H 0 : ρ 1 = ρ 2 , where now ρ j (j = 1, 2) is the correlation between Y and X j . This can be done with the R function TWOpov. When dealing with robust correlations, use the function twoDcorR.",
